{"type":"message","id":"e26c7857","parentId":"26e95d84","timestamp":"2026-03-19T18:10:24.755Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No MEMORY-LITE.md exists. The context is at 77%, which exceeds the 60% threshold. This is a proactive alert from the cron job. \n\nLooking at the context manager skill, when context exceeds threshold, I should save important memory and prepare for a session reset. But this is being run as a cron job - the user may not see this directly unless I report it.\n\nLet me check the HEARTBEAT.md to see if there's anything configured there, and also check the session state to see if there's active work.\n\nActually, looking at the AGENTS.md guidelines about heartbeats - I should be proactive but not annoying. The context at 77% is getting high but not critical. However, since this is a scheduled cron job specifically for context monitoring, I should report the findings and potentially suggest action.\n\nLet me check the proactivity memory to see if there are any active tasks or follow-ups I should be aware of.","thinkingSignature":"1eb171bb353d875b4bac1c100c72c0b3c046cf9e4680a78be8cb951e02f9c82b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_putxete47hqm_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\HEARTBEAT.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_putxete47hqm_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\proactivity\\memory.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1531,"output":267,"cacheRead":37099,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38897,"cost":{"input":0.0006124,"output":0.00040050000000000003,"cacheRead":0.00148396,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00249686}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773943817629}}
{"type":"message","id":"8e498aef","parentId":"e26c7857","timestamp":"2026-03-19T18:10:24.767Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_putxete47hqm_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# HEARTBEAT.md\n\n# Keep this file empty (or with only comments) to skip heartbeat API calls.\n\n# Add tasks below when you want the agent to check something periodically.\n\n## Context Manager Check\n\n- Run session_status to check current context usage\n- If context > 60%, consider saving memory and preparing for session switch\n- Check ~/proactivity/session-state.md for active tasks\n- Update ~/proactivity/memory/working-buffer.md if needed\n\n## Self-Improving Check\n\n- Read ./skills/self-improving/heartbeat-rules.md\n- Use ~/self-improving/heartbeat-state.md for last-run markers and action notes\n- If no file inside ~/self-improving/ changed since the last reviewed change, return HEARTBEAT_OK\n\n## Proactivity Check\n\n- Read ~/proactivity/heartbeat.md\n- Re-check active blockers, promised follow-ups, stale work, and missing decisions\n- Ask what useful check-in or next move would help right now\n- Message the user only when something changed or needs a decision\n- Update ~/proactivity/session-state.md after meaningful follow-through\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773943824765}}
