{"type":"message","id":"6e762eec","parentId":"fee13d64","timestamp":"2026-03-19T18:10:29.371Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So this is a context monitor alert. The context is at 77%, which is above the 60% threshold. Since this is a cron job that just checks and logs, I should probably just acknowledge this and potentially save important memory before the context gets too full.\n\nThe cron job already logged the warning. As the main agent, I should decide whether to act on this or let it be. Since the heartbeat says to \"consider saving memory and preparing for session switch\" when context > 60%, I should do that.\n\nLet me check the session-state to see if there's active work I should preserve first.","thinkingSignature":"d700ae12f1ee8f5c6b50cb061b913332ee26d47234f9d5cc9fe98a7101dd9a21"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1ikyii5j51r6_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\proactivity\\session-state.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2091,"output":164,"cacheRead":37099,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39354,"cost":{"input":0.0008364000000000001,"output":0.000246,"cacheRead":0.00148396,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00256636}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773943824769}}
