{"type":"message","id":"ff323f37","parentId":"a15f6cef","timestamp":"2026-03-19T18:10:41.939Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No active session state file, so there's no ongoing critical task I need to preserve. The context monitor has flagged that we're at 77% usage. According to the heartbeat guidelines, when context > 60%, I should consider saving memory and preparing for session switch.\n\nThe cron job already ran and alerted. Since there's no active work and no session state file, I should acknowledge the alert and maybe suggest to the user (董事长) that we might want to start a fresh session soon to avoid context exhaustion.\n\nActually, this is a cron job context monitor - the results go to the cron log. The cron job is just logging this, not sending a message to the user. As the main agent, I could potentially just acknowledge this in my logs and move on, since there's no active work to preserve.\n\nBut wait - the AGENTS.md says to be proactive. At 77%, we're getting high. The user might appreciate knowing this before context runs out. However, it's 2:10 AM - probably not the best time to message. Let me just log this and suggest a session reset soon.\n\nActually, looking at the cron context - this is running as a cron job context monitor. The cron job itself won't send a message to the user - it's just logging. As the main agent who received this cron context, I should process it and decide whether to act.\n\nSince there's no active work and it's late night (2:10 AM), I should probably just note this in my daily memory and move on. But I should at least acknowledge the alert came through.\n\nLet me create a brief daily memory note and acknowledge the state.","thinkingSignature":"a5d16a7be4344ffcf9fa9121df1f1b7393cf8ab89c8fd5db649e1176ba58319c"},{"type":"text","text":"**Context Monitor Alert Received** — 77% context usage detected (threshold: 60%)\n\nNo active session state or critical ongoing work found. Context is getting high but not yet critical. Recording this checkpoint and will monitor.\n\nAt this rate, a session refresh will be recommended soon. Not worth disturbing 董事长 at 2:10 AM over this — will handle proactively during next interaction or when usage approaches 85%.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p2cooba5e6nn_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# 2026-03-20 Daily Memory\n\n## Context Monitor Alerts\n- 02:10 — Context usage 77% (153920/200000 tokens), exceeded 60% threshold\n- No active session state or critical ongoing tasks\n- Recommended action: Session refresh soon (before 85%)\n\n## Notes\n- Late night (02:10 AM) — no user disturbance warranted\n- Will suggest context refresh at next natural interaction\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-20.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2318,"output":560,"cacheRead":37099,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39977,"cost":{"input":0.0009272000000000001,"output":0.00084,"cacheRead":0.00148396,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0032511600000000003}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773943829381}}
